<h4>Question <b id="current">18</b></h4>
            <p>A small quantity of solid ammonium chloride was heated gently in a test tube; the solid gradually disappeared to produce a mixture of two gases. Later a white cloudy deposit was observed on the cooler part of the test tube. The ammonium chloride is said to have undergone _______</p>
            <form>
            <label onclick="mod(18,'18a')"><b>a</b><input type="radio" name="one"><span id="18a">distillation</span></label><br><br>
            <label onclick="mod(18,'18b')"><b>b</b><input type="radio" name="one" ><span id="18b">sublimation</span></label><br><br>
            <label onclick="mod(18,'18c')"><b>c</b><input type="radio" name="one" > <span id="18c">precipitation</span></label><br><br>
            <label onclick="mod(18,'18d')"><b>d</b><input type="radio" name="one" ><span id="18d">evaporation</span></label><br><br>